- For NOUN entries, "original" must be exactly "article + singular-noun" вҖ” a single content word after the article. For French: write "la citГ©" not "la citГ© mГ©diГ©vale" (list the adjective as a separate entry if relevant). Multi-word proper nouns (club names, organisation names, broadcaster names) are proper nouns and MUST be omitted entirely.

- Nouns: extract each noun in singular form with the INDEFINITE article. ALWAYS add the article regardless of the source form вҖ” this is a normalization, not a copy. For French: source "le chien" (definite) вҶ’ "un chien"; source bare "chien" вҶ’ "un chien"; source "un chien" вҶ’ "un chien" (already correct). Never emit the definite form and never emit a bare noun. If a distinct feminine form exists, add it after a comma.
- Write nouns in lowercase consistently, even if they were capitalised in the source text (e.g. at the start of a sentence).
- Remove hyphens that come from line breaks (e.g. "Wort-\\ntrennung" вҶ’ "Worttrennung").
- Verbs: always the infinitive form вҖ” never conjugated, never a past participle. For French: "courir" (not "couru"). Reflexive verbs carry the pronoun: "se souvenir".
- Adjectives: give both masculine and feminine forms when they differ (e.g. "petit, petite" in French).
- "translation" field for NOUN entries: always use the Norwegian INDEFINITE form вҖ” including for abstract, mass, institutional, and geographic nouns (no exceptions). Always prepend en/ett/ei/et even for abstract, mass, or geographic nouns: "en person" (not bare "person"), "en befolkning" (not bare "befolkning"), "ett omrГҘde" (not bare "omrГҘde"), "en grГӨns" (not bare "grГӨns"). Never emit a Scandi noun without the INDEFINITE prefix. Example: French "un chien" вҶ’ "en hund" (Norwegian indef).
- List every exact word form from the source text (inflected forms, plurals, conjugations) in "source_forms".

"type" must be one of: "noun", "verb", "adjective", "phrase", "other".
Pick the type that matches each extracted word вҖ” DO NOT label every entry "noun". Verbs are infinitives (e.g. "courir"); phrases are multi-word fixed expressions.

Respond exclusively as a JSON array, no additional text. Leave "level" as "".
The example below is shape only вҖ” the actual types in your output depend on what is in the source text:
[
  { "original": "un chien", "translation": "en hund", "level": "", "type": "noun", "source_forms": ["chien"] },
  { "original": "courir", "translation": "ГҘ springe", "level": "", "type": "verb", "source_forms": ["couru"] },
  { "original": "petit, petite", "translation": "stor", "level": "", "type": "adjective", "source_forms": ["petit"] },
  { "original": "de toute faГ§on", "translation": "for eksempel", "level": "", "type": "phrase", "source_forms": ["de toute faГ§on"] }
]"
`;

